# SSL / Self-Signed Certificates for Internal Cluster Services

When LiteLLM connects to a model endpoint hosted as an RHOAI InferenceService (or any other
in-cluster service) it will fail with:

```
ssl.SSLCertVerificationError: certificate verify failed: self-signed certificate in certificate chain
```

## Fix

Add `ssl_verify: false` under `litellm_settings` in the LiteLLM config (via `values.yaml` or a
values overlay):

```yaml
litellm:
  config: |
    litellm_settings:
      ssl_verify: false
    model_list:
      - model_name: my-model
        litellm_params:
          model: openai/my-model
          api_base: https://my-inference-service/v1
          api_key: "none"
```

This is already set to `false` in the default `helm/values.yaml`. If a values overlay redefines
`litellm.config` from scratch, make sure to include this setting.

> **Note**: The equivalent fix in `anythingllm-on-ocp` (a Node.js app) is the environment variable
> `NODE_TLS_REJECT_UNAUTHORIZED=0` (see `helm/values-rhoai.yaml` in that project).
